explanation: The solution uses a priority queue to efficiently track the unmarked elements and their indices. It iterates through the queries, marking the specified element and then the k smallest unmarked elements. The priority queue allows for efficient retrieval of the smallest elements. The overall time complexity is dominated by the log n time complexity of the priority queue operations and the linear time complexity of iterating through the queries. The space complexity is O(n) due to the priority queue storing up to n elements.

